-2x-3y+9z&=-4,
\end{align*}

compute $x$. ||| Let w = 4y + 12z. The equations transform into \begin{align*} 3x + 4w &= 10, \\ -2x - 3w &= -4. \end{align*} Adding 3 times the second equation to 4 times the first equation gives 0 = 30, which shows that x = 5.

If

\begin{align*}
3x+4y-12z&=10,\\
-2x-3y+9z&=-4,
\end{align*}

compute $x$. ||| Replace y with 3z in the original equations to get \begin{align*} 3x + 12z - 12z &= 10, \\ -2x - 9z + 9z &= -4. \end{align*} This simplifies to 3x = 10, thus x = \boxed{10}.

