-x^2 - 1 &\text{if }x<0, \\
2&\text{if }0 \le x< 4, \\
\sqrt{x}&\text{if }x \ge 4.
\end{cases}
\]Find $f(\pi)$. ||| Since \(\pi\) is approximately 3.14, and it is greater than 4, we should use the third case of the function. Therefore, \(f(\pi) = \sqrt{\pi}\). So, \(f(\pi) = \boxed{\sqrt{\pi}}\).

