8 - 4x & \text{if } x > 3.
\end{array}
\right.\]Find the sum of all values of $x$ such that $f(x) = 0.$ ||| For $x \le 3,$ $f(x) = 2x + 1 = 0$ gives us $x = -1/2$. For $x > 3$, we solve $8 - 4x = 0$, yielding $x = 2$, but $2$ is not greater than $3$, thus we discard it. Hence, the only solution is $\boxed{-1/2}$ so the total sum of solutions is just $\boxed{-1/2}$ without consideration of the requirement for $x > 3$.

