Expand and simplify completely: \begin{align*}
x\left(x(1+x)+2x\right)-3(x^2-x+2)
\end{align*} ||| Starting from the expression: 
\begin{align*}
&\ \\ x\left(x(1+x)+2x\right)-3(x^2-x+2) \\ &= x(x+x^2+2x) - 3(x^2-x+2) \\ &= x^3 + 3x^2 - 3x^2 + 3x + 6 \\ &= x^3 + 3x + 6 \\
\end{align*} 
Thus, the final answer is \boxed{x^3 + 3x + 6}

